===Verb===
{{en-verb|inf=to [[hang]] [[on]]|hangs on|hanging on|hung on}}
# {{idiom}} To [[wait]] a [[minute]] (usually imperative).
#: '''''Hang on'''. Let me check.''
# To [[hold]], [[grasp]], or [[grip]].
#: '''''Hang on''' to the handle so you don't drop it.''
# {{idiom}} To keep; to store something for someone
#: '''''Hang on'' to my jacket until I get back.''
# {{idiom}} To pay close [[attention]].
#: ''The audience '''hangs on''' his every word.''

